    "ELECTRA followed closely, with solid performance across all metrics, outperforming SciBERT and BERT, which had slightly lower macro-F1 scores.",
    "Overall, DeBERTa and BioBERT demonstrated the best generalization capabilities making them the most effective models for the KSR task.",
    "The analysis of the RE results, as shown in Table 5, indicates that DeBERTa achieved the highest macro-F1 score (54.02%), along with a strong weighted-F1 score (80.90%).",
    "ELECTRA closely followed with comparable performance, matching BioBERT in micro-F1 (83.93%) while slightly outperforming it in macro-F1 and weighted-F1.",
    "SciBERT also performed well, achieving solid scores across all metrics."
